content:
Have you ever wondered&hellip;
 What are R projects, and why do I need to use them? Why is version control important for research projects? What tools are available to make github and R more user-friendly to a beginner?  In the Tottenham lab at Columbia, I held a workshop for graduate students and research assistants on these topics. The slides can be found here .
For more details on how to integrate github into your R workflow, check out Happy Git and GitHub for the useR by Jenny Bryan.
